Ski Areas

Browse an interactive table of the world’s ski areas.

Explore statistics on all named ski areas in the world with at least 3 runs and 50 meters of cumulative vertical drop across their runs. The underlying data is provided by OpenSkiMap and OpenStreetMap with statistics computed by https://github.com/dhimmel/openskistats.

Caution

OpenSkiStats is a work in progress. Methods and results are subject to change. Feedback is welcome via GitHub issues.

Table usage

Numeric columns support the filtering filters:

  • 15 for value ≥ 15
  • -20 for value ≤ 20
  • [10, 20] for 10 ≤ value ≤ 20
  • (10, 20) for 10 < value < 20
  • (, 5] for value ≤ 5
  • 80 (not 0.8) for a percent value ≥ 80%.

Ski run difficulty is collapsed and colored as follows:

  • easy combines novice and easy
  • intermediate combines intermediate
  • advanced combines advanced, expert, extreme, and freeride
  • other combines other and missing

Source data

OpenSkiMap data is from 2025-10-17.
